            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pat your<strong> sirloin steak[s]</strong> dry with<strong> </strong>kitchen paper, drizzle them with <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> on both sides</p><p>Once very hot, add the <strong>seasoned sirloin</strong> <strong>steak[s]</strong> to the pan</p><p>For rare, cook for 2-3 min max on each side; for medium-rare, cook for 3-4 min on each side; for medium, cook for 4-5 min on each side</p><p>Once the steak is cooked, transfer to a plate to rest</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1591624661118-x200.jpg",
